results.name: Numbers n such that the poset of multiset partitions of a multiset whose multiplicities are the prime indices of n is a lattice.
comment: This multiset (row n of A305936) is generally not the same as the multiset of prime indices of n. For example, the prime indices of 12 are {1,1,2}, while a multiset whose multiplicities are {1,1,2} is {1,1,2,3}.
reference: R. P Stanley, Enumerative Combinatorics Vol. 1, Sec. 3.3.
results.author: _Gus Wiseman_, Dec 05 2018
